pokedexEntries.red: An extremely rarely seen marine Pokémon. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.
pokedexEntries.blue: An extremely rarely seen marine Pokémon. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.
pokedexEntries.yellow: It is said that this Pokémon lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, it is only a rumor.
pokedexEntries.gold: It is said that this Pokémon constantly flies over the immense seas and rescues drowning people.
pokedexEntries.silver: This marine Pokémon has an impressive build that lets it freely fly over raging seas without trouble.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It is said that somewhere in the ocean lies an island where these gather. Only they live there.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just sixteen hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just sixteen hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.
pokedexEntries.emerald: It can circle the globe in just 16 hours. It is a kindhearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: It can fly in spite of its big and bulky physique. It circles the globe in just 16 hours.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Very few people ever see this Pokémon. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.
pokedexEntries.diamond: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

pokedexEntries.sun: This Pokémon saved a shipwrecked man, taking him to a remote island—a paradise occupied solely by Dragonite.
pokedexEntries.moon: Incur the wrath of this normally calm Pokémon at your peril, because it will smash everything to smithereens before it's satisfied.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It flies over raging seas as if they were nothing. Observing this, a ship’s captain dubbed this Pokémon “the sea incarnate.”
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: You’ll often hear tales of this kindhearted Pokémon rescuing people or Pokémon that are drowning.
